Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim are willing to pay almost $70million for Josh Hamilton to play in Texas  . 
  Hamilton filed for divorce from wife Katie in February and admitted to relapsing with drugs and alcohol . 
  The 33-year-old has about $83million left on his contract with the Angels . 
  He is going to be sent back to his former team the Texas Rangers . 
  The Rangers are only prepared to pay around $15million to Hamilton and do not want to give up any players . 
  Hamilton has a history of substance abuse and has been on the disabled list after shoulder surgery . 
  The Angels signed him to a five-year $125million deal in 2012 . 
 